data.title: Patrick Mahomes Goes Undercover on YouTube, Twitter and Instagram
data.meta_description: On this episode of Actually Me, Kansas City superstar quarterback Patrick Mahomes goes undercover on the Internet and responds to real comments from YouTube, Instagram, Twitter, Quora and Wikipedia. Does he really put ketchup on steak? What is his throwing release time?
data.text:
This is Patrick Mahomes

and I'm going undercover on the internet.

[light music]

This is Actually Me.

[light music]

First up, let's look at Twitter.

[light music]

If you could throw to one Hall of Fame receiver

who would it be and why?

It would probably be Randy Moss,

just 'cause to have that size, that speed, that athleticism,

probably just throw it as far as I could,

kinda like I do with Tyreek a little bit

and he can go get it.

[bird chirping]

Next, if Patrick Mahomes wins one

more Super Bowl in his career,

does that put him about Aaron Rodgers for all time?

So I don't know if a lot of people remember

the beginning of Aaron Rodgers' career,

but I mean, he went to the Super Bowl and made a lot of

the same and more throws that I made,

I mean he's one of the best all time,

he's someone that I take a lot of stuff from.

So, to me, I'm just trying to get somewhere close

by the end of my career to where he is.

So, to be around that by the end of my career,

that would be the goal.

Has BrittanyLynne8 wore you out with all those workouts?

Uh, 100%, she's killed me with the workouts,

especially at the beginning.

Here, let me show you how I've been workin' out.

The amount of reps, like is unreal.

I have to like stop doin' all the reps sometimes.

Resistance bands, kettle bells, dumbbells,

just gettin' after it,

she's used to workin' out at homes, definitely not me.

Could Patrick Mahomes have played basketball at KU?

The real answer is absolutely not,

but in my mind I think I could have.

Maybe walk on and be a benchwarmer,

I could do that if you want,

submit. [bird chirping]

Next up, we got Quora.

[light music]

Did Patrick Mahomes break the Madden curse?

Apparently there's a curse if you're on the cover of Madden,

that you get injured or something happens to you

that next season, I don't know if I broke it,

but I definitely battled it for a little bit of time there

and then came out on top,

so I don't know if it's actually true

but I did get hurt, came back from it

and got to win the Super Bowl so I mean

I at least got through it and beat it there in the end.

What is Patrick Mahomes' throwing release time?

I have zero idea,

as long as it's fast enough to not get intercepted,

I'll take that.

Why can't Patrick Mahomes play pickup basketball anymore?

So, I was playin' pickup basketball,

got posted online, we got a call from my GM

Brett Veach and it wasn't like,

you can't play, but it was like I would really not like

you to play, so when it comes from that guy,

that's almost like yeah, you can't play.

I knew when they posted the video I was gonna get

in trouble because they tagged Bleacher Report,

it was fun while it lasted, next.

In an NFL commercial, Patrick Mahomes puts ketchup

on a steak, is that really something people do?

I don't know if it's really something that people do,

but that is really something that I do.

Like, 100%, I had steak last night,

and I put ketchup on it.

It was like a ribeye, like expensive steak

and then it made it even better,

I threw a little bit of ketchup on the side

so if you haven't tried it,

I would try it because it is delicious.

Will Patrick Mahomes become the GOAT?

It's pretty early on in my career to be sayin'

anything like that obviously I've had a good start

to the career but to be the GOAT

you have to be consistent through your entire career

playin' at a high level

and there's some guys in the NFL

and in all other sports that have done it

so I have a very long ways to go.

All right, movin' on to Instagram.

It's Actually Me.

What throwing mechanics did you learn from

your father and applied to your game?

Playin' baseball I used to do side arm,

you see all the different type of stuff where I'm like

throwin' it from different arm angles.

Long toss with my dad built arm strength,

and it taught me that you can't always throw

from the perfect platform and you have to still be accurate

so that definitely applies to my football game.

What video games do you like the most?

And are you into streaming or watching streamers?

So my favorite video game is Call of Duty,

I've been big on Call of Duty since like

I was in high school, like freshman year of high school,

eighth grade even maybe.

I've always been a Call of Duty fan,

I play Madden obviously.

I play 2K, I play a lot of the sports games.

And to answer your second question,

I don't stream, just 'cause I feel like

I'm good but not that good.

And so, I don't stream, but I'll watch streamers

every once and a while but I can't sit there

for more than like five to 10 minutes watching them

like I don't see how people can sit for like hours

and watch people just play video games, next.

How's your knee doing?

Looking great man!

So my knee has been doing awesome,

obviously I've been working with it all off season,

like I did during the season

but I actually feel like all the work that I've put in

for injury prevention on my knee that I'm actually

probably stronger than it was before

as far as my quad and hip flexor and everything like that

that holds that kneecap in place

and I mean, I do so much extra work on that stuff

just to obviously with the injury that I've had

that I feel like i'mm stronger than ever with those muscles.

Yeah so the specific exercises that I do are like

a lot of like single leg squats,

single leg raisers, a lot of that stuff

is really building those muscles, builds that quad,

it really holds that kneecap in place.

So it's just Armani, a picture of when I'm in my suits.

All of my suits I get custom made by a guy

that is out of Dallas, Texas.

Actually he's from Tyler Texas my hometown

and he made me my first suit for me

for my draft day party so I kinda just stayed with him

and he does a great job, his names Preston.

He does a great job of keeping my suits clean

and keeping me one of the freshest on the field at all times

More Twitter, man gets a Patrick Mahomes Champ Stamp tattoo.

Yeah, so this was the weirdest probably moment

I've ever had with a fan interaction,

I remember goin' on Kimmel and no one tellin' me

he was literally just sitting in the first row

and they were like ey, we wanna show you something

and it was a dude with almost a life size portrait

of me on his back and I was literally

sitting there goin' what in the world did I just get into.

[bird chirping]

Actually, it looked better in person than it did

on TV I think but it was,

I don't think y'all realize how big it was,

like it was a big, it wasn't a little tattoo at all.

Who do you think is the best player at their respective

sports is it LeBron James in basketball,

Patrick Mahomes in football or Mike Trout in baseball?

Taking me out of this, first off,

both these other guys have multiple MVPs,

been at the top of the sport for a long time.

[bird chirping]

I would give it to LeBron right now,

just 'cause he's done it for longer than Mike has

even though Mike has done it for a long time

and is a beast on the baseball field.

He has been at the top of the game

since he's entered the league at 18,

now 17 years in he's still top of the game,

so I mean definitely have to give him the nod.

[bird chirping]

Posted!

What would your reaction be if Patrick Mahomes retired

from the Kansas City Chiefs and signed a contract

with the Kansas City Royals?

Well definitely nothing that would happen any time soon,

I'm lovin' football, lovin' playin' for the Chiefs,

I mean I'm never gonna throw anything out so maybe one day.

[bird chirping]

Off the top of your head,

do you remember every player selected before

you in the NFL draft?

Let's see, Miles Garret was one.

Two was Mitchell Trubisky.

Three, Solomon Thomas.

Four, who picked fourth?

I wanna say Leonard Fournette?

Five

I can't remember who went fifth,

but I know for sure I got four of them.

Christian McCaffrey went in front of me,

John Ross, Corey Davis, Jamal Adams,

I'm missing one person, I can't,

y'all have to give it to me,

I can't remember the one person that went before me.

Sorry, but I got eight of the nine

people that went before me.

[bird chirping]

I'm making a new playlist for when I go running and workout.

What are some songs that get you hype before a game?

So I kinda bounce around,

I listen to all J. Cole.

All Chance the rapper, I listen to Meek Mill,

Drake obviously, I use an app called EarBuds,

which it shares my playlist

so if you ever wanna tune in and listen with me

before games go ahead and tune in.

Wikipedia.

[light music]

Coming out of Texas Tech, Mahomes was projected as a

first or second round pick by the majority of analysts

and scouts during the throwing drills at the

NFL Scouting Combine, Patrick Mahomes' passes were clocked

at 60 miles an hour, tying Logan Thomas and Bryan Bennett

for the fastest pass ever recorded at the NFL Combine.

So the second part of that,

I was clocked at 60 mile an hour at the Combine,

that was cool, I wanted to get 60,

that was my threshold, I wanted to get into that,

'cause no other quarterback has ever really got there

except for those couple guys

and then, I guess some analysts had me as a first second

round pick when I actually turned in my like draft grade,

you can turn in and get a projection from the NFL,

they said second or third round pick

and I was like man, I'm goin' in the first round

and that was my mindset.

And so, even though analysts said first second round,

I had gotten a second or third round grade back,

and I did what I, I trained hard and impressed enough

coaches that I got drafted in the first round.

More Instagram.

How does your workouts change during

the season versus the off season?

So that's actually a great question,

I believe during the season it's all about maintaining

the injury prevention so I do two, three workouts a week,

and it's all about keeping that strength,

keeping that mobility and keeping all those things ready

so that you go out there and can perform at your best

and then off season, it's all about,

I start off the off season kind of building

and then I try to cut down for the season.

I'm kind of in that starting of the cut now

but I try to get some muscle on me,

get bigger, lift a little bit heavier,

and then as I get closer to the season I cut down

and try to get myself prepared to go through

the season and be at my best.

And here, I'll show you a little bit, so roll the tape.

‚ô™ Never settle ‚ô™

‚ô™ I got Henny all in my cup ‚ô™

‚ô™ I'm on top ‚ô™

‚ô™ I'm on the level yeah ‚ô™

‚ô™ I'm tryin' to get to the back ‚ô™

‚ô™ Got it on lock ‚ô™

‚ô™ Got it on smash yeah ‚ô™

‚ô™ She tryin' to holler what's up ‚ô™

‚ô™ I want that ‚ô™

‚ô™ That's how it is yeah ‚ô™

‚ô™ We on our way up ‚ô™

‚ô™ I'm on my way I'm on my way I'm on my way up ‚ô™

I gotta ask, how did it feel to be down

late in the Super Bowl?

Well it didn't feel good, I'll tell you that.

When it was like six, seven minutes left

and we were down two scores,

that's when you started getting to that time

where you're like we gotta do something right now.

It was surreal, I never had doubt that we were gonna win

but I for sure was like man we're runnin' out of time.

But to find a way to win that game

is something I'll be able to relive the rest of my life.

Did Pat drop 10 to 15 pounds?

Looks more athletic in this shot, talented young man.

So I did not drop 10 to 15 pounds,

but I appreciate the compliment.

But no, I'm still right at where I was around season,

I usually try to stay in that 225 range.

Like I said, at the beginning of the off season,

I get up to like 230, 232, build up

and then I try to by season be about 225

and I think this morning I weighed in at 228.

So, I'm on that drop right now,

I'm getting back down to that right weight.

What is your choice of shoe for workout?

Obviously I'm an Adidas athlete, so Adidas.

I wear all type of different Adidas shoes,

I wear the human races or the alpha bounces,

pretty much anything Adidas.

Hopefully, stuff will keep evolving with Adidas shoes

and keep getting better and better workout shoes

and have the best workout shoes, all time.

And so I wear every type of Adidas

and I love them to work out in.

Hey Pat, what was your favorite moment

at playing at Texas Tech?

My favorite moment was my sophomore year,

we played Texas at Texas on Thanksgiving day

and so it was kind of that only Thanksgiving day game on

and we came back and we won't at the end of the game

in Austin and not a lot of quarterbacks win in Austin

at Texas Tech, they used to be the powerhouse in Texas

and so to win that game at Texas and on Thanksgiving day

it was definitely my favorite moment.

YouTube. [light music]

You may not believe it, but it's actually me.

So Mahomes can throw a 95 plus mile an hour fastball?

That's faster than most MLB pitchers.

Yeah, well I could throw one,

back in the day I hit 96 at the state championship

when I was a junior in high school

but I don't know about these days,

I mean I would have to get back into shape and everything

like that but I did hit 96,

so that's pretty fast, I probably got a couple home runs

hit off me in the MLB if I was there.

What is it with athletes and shoes?

[laughs] That is a very true statement,

a whole lot of athletes loves shoes.

It's probably 'cause we have to wear a ton of 'em

but for me, I've always loved shoes,

I've always kept like every single pair of shoes

that I got clean then obviously getting into the NFL,

sign with Adidas, I kind of got my free range of shoes

and I got all of them.

Yeah, so the last time I counted I had over 200

and I've gotten more so probably like 220, 230 range

but I do a good job of, once I stop wearing,

there's certain shoes I stop wearing,

I usually give them to family members or friends

that wear the same size as me.

So we had a lot of great questions,

some were way out there, some of them were good,

I'm glad we got them all answered,

y'all can really understand where I'm coming from,

that's it, thank y'all.
